	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Shavuot</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Shavuot#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="Shavuot#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Jewish holiday</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For the Talmudical tractate, see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shevu%27ot" title="Shevu&#39;ot">Shevu'ot</a>.</div>
<table class="infobox vevent" style="width:22em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" class="hd" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color: lightskyblue">Shavuоt</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_(Pentecost)_(Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest)_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Moritz Daniel Oppenheim - Shavuot (Pentecost) (Das Wochen- oder Pfingst-Fest) - Google Art Project.jpg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_%28Pentecost%29_%28Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest%29_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg/240px-Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_%28Pentecost%29_%28Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest%29_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg" decoding="async" width="240" height="283" srcset="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_%28Pentecost%29_%28Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest%29_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg/360px-Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_%28Pentecost%29_%28Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest%29_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg 1.5x, http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_%28Pentecost%29_%28Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest%29_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg/480px-Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim_-_Shavuot_%28Pentecost%29_%28Das_Wochen-_oder_Pfingst-Fest%29_-_Google_Art_Project.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3443" data-file-height="4060" /></a><div style="caption"><i>Shavuot</i> by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moritz_Daniel_Oppenheim" title="Moritz Daniel Oppenheim">Moritz Daniel Oppenheim</a></div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Official name</th><td><a href="Hebrew_language" title="Hebrew language">Hebrew</a>: <span lang="he" dir="rtl">שבועות or חג השבועות</span>&#8206; (<i>Ḥag HaShavuot</i> or <i>Shavuot</i>)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Also called</th><td>English: "Feast of Weeks"</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Observed&#160;by</th><td><a href="Jews" title="Jews">Jews</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Type</th><td>Jewish</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Significance</th><td class="summary">One of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Pilgrimage_Festivals" title="Three Pilgrimage Festivals">Three Pilgrimage Festivals</a>. Celebrates the revelation of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chumash_(Judaism)" title="Chumash (Judaism)">Five Books of the Torah</a> by <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Names_of_God_in_Judaism" title="Names of God in Judaism">God</a> to <a href="Moses" title="Moses">Moses</a> and to the <a href="Israelites" title="Israelites">Israelites</a> at <a href="Biblical_Mount_Sinai" class="mw-redirect" title="Biblical Mount Sinai">biblical Mount Sinai</a>, 49 days (7 weeks) after <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Exodus" title="The Exodus">the Exodus</a> from <a href="Ancient_Egypt" title="Ancient Egypt">ancient Egypt</a>. Commemorates the wheat harvesting in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Land_of_Israel" title="Land of Israel">Land of Israel</a>. Culmination of the 49 days of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Counting_of_the_Omer" title="Counting of the Omer">Counting of the Omer</a>.</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Celebrations</th><td>Festive meals. All-night <a href="Torah" title="Torah">Torah</a> study. Recital of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akdamut" title="Akdamut">Akdamut</a> liturgical poem in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashkenazi_Jews" title="Ashkenazi Jews">Ashkenazic</a> synagogues. Reading of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Ruth" title="Book of Ruth">Book of Ruth</a>. Eating of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dairy" title="Dairy">dairy</a> products. Decoration of homes and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Synagogue" title="Synagogue">synagogues</a> with greenery (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orach_Chayim" title="Orach Chayim">Orach Chayim</a>, <a class="external text" href="https://he.wikisource.org/wiki/%D7%A9%D7%95%D7%9C%D7%97%D7%9F_%D7%A2%D7%A8%D7%95%D7%9A_%D7%90%D7%95%D7%A8%D7%97_%D7%97%D7%99%D7%99%D7%9D_%D7%AA%D7%A6%D7%93_%D7%90">494</a>).</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Begins</th><td>the 6th day of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sivan" title="Sivan">Sivan</a> (or the Sunday following the 6th day of Sivan in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karaite_Judaism" title="Karaite Judaism">Karaite Judaism</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Ends</th><td>7th (in <a href="Israel" title="Israel">Israel</a>: 6th) day of Sivan</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Date</th><td>6 Sivan</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">2019&#160;date</th><td>Sunset, 8 June –<br />nightfall, 10 June</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">2020&#160;date</th><td>Sunset, 28 May –<br />nightfall, 30 May<sup id="cite_ref-Shavuot_dates_1-0" class="reference"><a href="Shavuot#cite_note-Shavuot_dates-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">2021&#160;date</th><td>Sunset, 16 May –<br />nightfall, 18 May</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">2022&#160;date</th><td>Sunset, 4 June –<br />nightfall, 6 June</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Related&#160;to</th><td><a href="Passover" title="Passover">Passover</a>, which precedes Shavuot</td></tr></tbody></table>
