<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Shavuot#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The other four are the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Lamentations" title="Book of Lamentations">Book of Lamentations</a>, read on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tisha_B%27Av" title="Tisha B&#39;Av">Tisha B'Av</a>; the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Ecclesiastes" class="mw-redirect" title="Book of Ecclesiastes">Book of Ecclesiastes</a>, read on <a href="Sukkot" title="Sukkot">Sukkot</a>; the <a href="Book_of_Esther" title="Book of Esther">Book of Esther</a> (<i>Megillat Esther</i>) read on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Purim" title="Purim">Purim</a>; and the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Song_of_Solomon" class="mw-redirect" title="Song of Solomon">Song of Songs</a>, the reading for Passover. See <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five_Megillot" title="Five Megillot">Five Megillot</a> for further details.</span>
</li>
